<img src="http://members.aol.com/italrishguy/thorjuly.jpg">
</center> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=alandrelmesmer>Alandrel Mesmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 6:50:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11682.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hand to Hand weapon help</span><hr size=1> Turn off all the new models. Cut your clipping plane back. Should solve your lag issue if it's video related. Can also /showspellseffects off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uscaliagluon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scalia Gluon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 9:07:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11682.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hand to Hand weapon help</span><hr size=1> HTH weapons tend to be more expensive and rare than 1HB weapons. Since you have a very good (but rather heavy) 1HB weapon in your primary hand, my guess is that you won't be able to find any HTH weapons of the same caliber in that price range.<br>
<br>
I'd go with a decent 1HB in your off hand, for example an SoS if you have the cash and can handle the weight, or an Etched Steel Baton/Knuckle Duster otherwise. Then, after gaining a couple more levels, I'd bag the 1HB weapons, dust off that PSU (better yet, get a Fist of Wood, 5/20), go to DL and shout that you are working on your skills and will help any group with extra DPS. You won't be able to KS them and your HTH will go up relatively quickly.<br>
<br>
Regarding the Range item issue, there are some display bugs which may  result in your character's model showing the item that is equipped in your Range slot if you are not holding a weapon. It has nothing to do with what can and cannot be equipped. And yes, the Goranga Idol is the way to go. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71792 target=_blank>Scalia</a> /  <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71783 target =_blank>Gluon</a> on E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wubao>Wubao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1537<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 9:16:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11682.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> good H2H weapon at level 40 ...</span><hr size=1> YOUR NAKED FIST.<br>
<br>
No, really, it is. And it's damn cheap too.<br>
<br>
-Wu<br>
Fist of Agnost the Indifferent <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utaigeforfeit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taige Forfeit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~damus28/_uimages/t2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 3:08:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11682.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: good H2H weapon at level 40 ...</span><hr size=1> People gasp when they see a L47 Monk using a fist/kd.  I'm not epic'd either(Duh).  I like the lack of weight though... <p>~Taige Forfeit~   <br>
<br>
